    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="606"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/799: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-22T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 22, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 23—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1042. Your 924, April 23 [<hi rend="italic">22?</hi>], 10 a.m. While I do not
                    feel now that we should delay furnishing aviation gasoline until concession for
                    airline granted, we might say at same time we agree to furnish it that we expect
                    facilities to be given for American airline to operate in Spain in international
                    service upon request. Are we interested in local passenger service between Spain
                    and Portugal or merely in trans-Atlantic passengers?</p>
                <p>I should like authority to sound out Foreign Office informally on general
                    subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
